SUMMARY:Housing Justice Happy Hour
DESCRIPTION:Join the Housing Justice Working Group for our monthly social event at Queen Anne Beerhall. This is a low-key chance to build community\, meet new people\, and chat with others who care about housing justice in Seattle. \nWe’ll be hanging out from 5:30pm–7:30 PM! Arrive before 6:00 PM to catch happy hour prices. The Beerhall also serves food\, including $5.99 tacos on Tuesdays\, so you can grab a bite while you connect with folks from the working group. \nAt 7:30\, trivia night starts—stick around if you want to form a team with a few fellow DSA members and maybe take home some bragging rights. \nThere are several bus stops nearby\, and there’s also a paid parking lot behind the bar if you’re driving. \nWhether you’re already involved with the housing justice workgroup or just curious and want to meet people\, all are welcome! Come say hi\, bring a friend\, and hang out with us! 🏠🍻
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/housing-justice-happy-hour-2/
LOCATION:Queen Anne Beer Hall\, 203 W Thomas St\, Seattle\, WA\, 98119\, United States
CATEGORIES:Housing,New Member Friendly,Socials
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://seattledsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/sdsa_housing_justice_working_group.png
GEO:47.6207814;-122.3597316
